+{"id":"bd-1kwk4","title":"[Reliability] Add timeout + kill for setup installer","description":"## Issue\\nSetup tool installation spawns \"bash -c\" for installer scripts without a timeout. A hung installer can block the request indefinitely and tie up resources.\\n\\n## Evidence\\n- apps/gateway/src/services/setup.service.ts:721-747 (Bun.spawn installCmd, no timeout/kill)\\n\\n## Impact\\nStuck installations can stall the setup API and accumulate long-running processes.\\n\\n## Recommended Fix\\n- Add a configurable timeout for installer runs (e.g., env or constant).\\n- On timeout, kill the process and surface a clear error.\\n- Emit progress status \"failed\" with timeout message.","status":"in_progress","priority":2,"issue_type":"task","assignee":"WindyCrane","created_at":"2026-01-30T17:37:19.292106739Z","created_by":"ubuntu","updated_at":"2026-01-30T17:41:26.258059255Z","compaction_level":0,"original_size":0}
