+{"id":"bd-3njv9","title":"[Reliability] Kill timed-out health check processes","description":"## Issue\\n/health detailed CLI checks set a timeout but do not kill the spawned process when the timeout fires. This can leave orphaned CLI processes running and consuming resources.\\n\\n## Evidence\\n- apps/gateway/src/routes/health.ts:224-257 (checkCLI sets timeout and rejects without proc.kill)\\n\\n## Impact\\nRepeated timeouts can accumulate stray processes, degrading system performance and skewing health results.\\n\\n## Recommended Fix\\n- On timeout, call proc.kill() (or proc.kill(\"SIGKILL\")) before rejecting.\\n- Consider capturing stdout safely after kill to avoid hanging reads.\\n- Add a regression test around timeout behavior if feasible.","status":"closed","priority":2,"issue_type":"bug","created_at":"2026-01-30T17:37:06.962047924Z","created_by":"ubuntu","updated_at":"2026-01-30T17:40:12.556029381Z","closed_at":"2026-01-30T17:40:12.555963409Z","close_reason":"Completed","compaction_level":0,"original_size":0}
